A more recent study, as described above, concluded with a 4.8-day incubation period (3.0-7.2) according to a demographic of 8,866 cases.
It is very important that sanitary authorities adjust the effective duration of quarantine after the most precise possible incubation period, in order to prevent infected but asymptomatic people from transmitting the virus.
