Although SARS-COV-2 has a tropism for the epithelial cells of the respiratory pathways expressing ACE-2, severe COVID-19 patients have symptoms of systemic hyperinflammation.
These are particularly GM-CSF secretary T cells that have been associated with the recruitment of inflammatory monocytes secreting IL6 and severe pulmonary pathology of COVID-19 patients.
